This paper deals with the optimization of content delivery over wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of stochastic optimization and Markov decision processes, which are topics that fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively. Additionally, the paper deals with caching and multicasting, which are topics that fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
